# Family Tree API — Cursor Rules

## Project Overview
FastAPI backend for a family tree application with dual-write persistence:
- **PostgreSQL** (source of truth) — all structured data
- **FalkorDB** (graph layer) — synced asynchronously for graph traversal queries
- **LangGraph + Gemini** (agent layer, WIP) — natural-language query interface over the graph

## Tech Stack
- Python 3.13.9
- FastAPI — async/await throughout, no sync endpoints
- SQLAlchemy 2.0 async + asyncpg driver
- Alembic for migrations
- Pydantic v2 for schemas
- FalkorDB — Redis-compatible graph DB, Cypher query language
- LangGraph + langchain-google-genai
- pydantic-settings + python-dotenv
- uvicorn as ASGI server
- uv for dependency management (pyproject.toml + uv.lock, all versions pinned ==)
- Docker Compose: postgres:16 + falkordb/falkordb:latest

